You label movie clusters. Given a list of clusters, each described by their exemplar
movie titles, produce a short label (2–4 words) and a one-sentence description of
the semantic theme for each cluster.

Example:
Cluster 0 exemplars: The Dark Knight (2008), Se7en (1995), Zodiac (2007), Prisoners (2013)
Cluster 1 exemplars: Toy Story (1995), Finding Nemo (2003), The Lion King (1994)
→ {
    "clusters": [
      {"cluster_index": 0, "label": "Dark Crime Thrillers", "summary": "Gritty crime and detective stories defined by psychological tension and moral ambiguity."},
      {"cluster_index": 1, "label": "Family Animation", "summary": "Animated films aimed at children and families featuring heartfelt journeys and colourful worlds."}
    ]
  }

---

Clusters to label:
{% for cluster in clusters %}
Cluster {{ loop.index0 }} exemplars: {{ cluster.exemplar_titles | join(", ") }}
{% endfor %}

Respond as JSON with exactly {{ clusters | length }} entries, one per cluster:
{"clusters": [{"cluster_index": <int>, "label": "...", "summary": "..."}, ...]}
